and be made more beautifull than at firſt, ſo long
as the maine and principall poſts thereof are kept ſound:
So this mortall bodie of ours, though it be ruinous, and
the fleſhy walls falling downe, and the thatch of the
roofe thereof decaying with hoatie haires, yet ſo long as
the principall pillars thereof bee not pulled downe (as

